1. Difference between Shift Left and Shift Right Testing
Shift Left testing focuses on early testing in SDLC.
It includes requirement review, unit, and integration testing.
Shift Right testing happens after deployment.
It includes monitoring, production validation, and user feedback.
Goal is early prevention vs real-time quality improvement.

2. Explain Continuous Testing
Continuous testing is testing throughout the CI/CD pipeline.
Tests run automatically on every code change.
Provides quick feedback to developers.
Ensures quality at every stage of delivery.
Supports faster and reliable releases.